metadata.name: RE/Posizioni #51
metadata.description:
Exactly one year ago I was minting my first fxhash project. 
‚ÄúPosizioni‚Äù was a quick sketch of only 25 editions that I put together to test this new platform and to my great surprise, it was the start of an amazing journey in this space that still continues to amaze me every day. 

‚ÄúRE/Posizioni‚Äù is an ideal continuation of my personal path that started one year ago: I decided to create an animated, glitchy, or even broken piece, something completely different from what I usually do as an artist and as a coder (and probably something I‚Äôm not very good at, forgive me for this :D ).
Even if this NFT crazy world is often uncertain, insecure, or unstable, we need to find a balance no matter how difficult, just as the lines in this artwork try to do.

Going out of my comfort zone, experimenting, or just having fun is what keeps this creative practice enjoyable for me, and it‚Äôs all that matters.

----

- Mouse click to pause the animation
- "s" key to download a png
- "f" key to full screen

Tested on Desktop/Chrome.
See LICENSE.md for more licensing details.

metadata.name: Constellation Of Happiness #237
metadata.description:
Constellation Of Happiness is a collaborative art project between NFT artists Kato Trofimova and Andrew Erickson.

Feeling happy is tough this year but it'll be much easier when you get your own constellation of happiness! Using expressionistic code art, Constellation Of Happiness channels the purest festive emotions a person can experience, for example, when tasting champagne bubbles or seeing and touching confetti. All these are turned into beautiful constellations of happiness using the aesthetics of star maps and carefully brought to your NFT collection.

2022

Kato Trofimova (Latvia) is an illustrator, visual artist, and creative director known for her love of minimalistic shapes and bright palettes. In her art, Kato questions boundaries between styles and stays optimistic no matter what.

Andrew Erickson (Switzerland) is a generative artist experimenting with various abstract styles. Be it delicate monochromatic line art or colorful gradient minimalism, Andrew is very good at coding any kind of digital beauty.

Hit 'p' in live mode to save a 9922‚Ää√ó‚Ää14032px PNG (for printing up to A0)
Hit 's' in live mode to save a plottable SVG

10% of proceeds go to support Processing.org

License: CC BY-NC-SA-4.0

metadata.name: FORMAT #32
metadata.description:
A generative animated artwork by Unruly Unroll, 2022.  
Custom HTML, JavaScript and GLSL code.

This artwork is responsive and the canvas will adapt to the size and orientation of the browser window.

Interaction on desktop :
- Press the 'SPACE' key to pause/unpause the animation.
- Press the 'S' key to save the current frame to a PNG file.  
- Press the 'F' key or double-click to switch to full screen mode.  
- Press the 'ESC' key to exit full screen mode.  

Interaction on mobile :
- Tap the screen to pause/unpause the animation.
- Double-tap the screen to switch to full screen mode.  
- Tap the back button to exit full screen mode.

@UnrulyUnroll

metadata.name: ZigZag #29
metadata.description:
‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ ZigZag ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ

‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ
Wikipedia
‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ

A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ü§ì

There's a chance no lines are shown at all, this is intentional, as I love "bugs" ü™≤

‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ

[b] toggle border
[n] toggle noise
[h] generate high res version
[s] save image

‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ
Education - back to 1994
‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ

Zig and Zag are also 2 puppets, have a look here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zig_and_Zag_(puppets)
There's this amazing song if you don't know called "Zig & Zag - Them Girls Them Girls".
You can view it on Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7bv_36P_f-w

‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ‚åÑ‚åÉ
